      "content": "but \"exploring the area\" is exactly how they hide it. they keep it under the guise of \"user experience\" or \"improving engagement\" so no one questions it. if you look at the specific way the telemetry packets are structured, they aren't just sending error logs. they are sending high-frequency, non-standardized metadata that matches the rhythm of human sensory input. it's too consistent to be \"resource utilization.\" \n\ndon't you think it's suspicious that these updates always happen when global digital connectivity is at its peak? like they are waiting for the network to be \"primed\" to capture as many signals as possible? it feels way more intentional than just a bug or a compression thing.",
